To use **Ansible with Amazon Web Services and store files in an Amazon S3 bucket, you can create the bucket and upload files using an Ansible playbook.


---

1. Install Required Packages

Install Ansible and AWS libraries:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible -y
pip install boto boto3

Install AWS Ansible collection:

ansible-galaxy collection install amazon.aws


---

2. Configure AWS Credentials

Run:

aws configure

Enter your credentials:

AWS Access Key ID: XXXXX
AWS Secret Access Key: XXXXX
Default region: us-east-1
Output format: json


---

3. Ansible Playbook to Create S3 Bucket and Upload File

Create a file called s3_bucket.yml

---
- name: Create S3 bucket and upload file
  hosts: localhost
  connection: local
  gather_facts: no

  tasks:

    - name: Create S3 bucket
      amazon.aws.s3_bucket:
        name: my-ansible-storage-bucket-2026
        state: present
        region: us-east-1

    - name: Upload file to S3 bucket
      amazon.aws.aws_s3:
        bucket: my-ansible-storage-bucket-2026
        object: sample.txt
        src: /home/ubuntu/sample.txt
        mode: put


---

4. Run the Playbook

Execute:

ansible-playbook s3_bucket.yml


---

5. Result

After running the playbook:

A new S3 bucket will be created in AWS.

The file sample.txt will be uploaded into the bucket.


So Ansible automates AWS storage management by creating an S3 bucket and storing files inside it automatically.


